Commands
Default prefix for me is !
This manual shows commands with the default prefix. If you are using a custom prefix,
please replace the ! with the one you are using.

Recipe:
Adds a recipe to the tracker. If the recipe exists, it it overwritten.
Syntax: !recipe <name> <ingredients> = <result>
Where:
- name: Name of the recipe
- ingredients: Ingredients in the recipe. Include the number of each with -n
- result: The item resulting from the recipe. Include number with -n
Example: !recipe cake flour-2 milk-1 chocolate-1 = chocolate_cake

Delete:
Deletes a recipe from the tracker by name. If multiple names are included, they will all be deleted.
Syntax: !delete <name1> [name2] ...
Where:
- name1: Name of the recipe, required
- name2...: Name of the recipe, optional
Example: !delete cake

Calculate:
Calculates the ingredients required for a recipe.
Syntax: !calculate <name> <number> [layers]
Where:
- name: Name of the recipe
- number: The number of the output items to calculate. Must be >= 1.
- layers: The layers down the recipe to calculate. Max of 25, must be >= 1.
If there are branching options, the bot will
ask you for the recipe to follow.
Example: !calculate cake 1 3

Get:
Gets a recipe from the tracker by name and shows the recipe.
Syntax: !get <name>
Where:
- name: Name of the recipe
Example: !get cake

List:
Lists all of the recipes in the tracker for the current server.
Syntax: !list
Example: !list

Clear_Calculation:
Clears the current branching calculation in the cache.
Syntax: !clear_calculation

Choose_Recipe:
Choose the recipe you want the current branching calculation to follow.
Syntax: !choose_recipe <name>
Where:
- name: Name of the recipe to choose
Example: !choose_recipe cake

Set_Prefix:
Sets my command prefix.
Syntax: !set_prefix <prefix>
Where -prefix: My new prefix
Example: !set_prefix -


Help:
Displays this manual.
Syntax: !help


